    {
      "title": "The Verbal Noun (المصدر)",
      "titleArabic": "المصدر",
      "content": [
        "The verbal noun (مصدر) is a noun that expresses the action itself without reference to time or person. Every verb has at least one مصدر.",
        "For Form I verbs, مصدر patterns are mostly irregular and must be memorized. Common patterns include فِعَالَة، فُعُول، فَعْل."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "كِتَابَة (writing) from كَتَبَ (to write)",
        "ذَهَاب (going) from ذَهَبَ (to go)",
        "قِرَاءَة (reading) from قَرَأَ (to read)",
        "جُلُوس (sitting) from جَلَسَ (to sit)",
        "دُخُول (entering) from دَخَلَ (to enter)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "الْكِتَابَةُ مُهِمَّةٌ", "english": "Writing is important" },
        { "arabic": "الْقِرَاءَةُ مُفِيدَةٌ", "english": "Reading is beneficial" },
        { "arabic": "أُحِبُّ التَّعَلُّمَ", "english": "I love learning" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Common Masdar Patterns",
      "titleArabic": "أوزان المصدر الشائعة",
      "content": [
        "While Form I masdars are mostly irregular, there are some common patterns to recognize."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "فِعَالَة - often for professions/crafts: كِتَابَة، قِرَاءَة",
        "فُعُول - common pattern: دُخُول، جُلُوس، خُرُوج",
        "فَعْل - simple actions: فَهْم (understanding), عِلْم (knowledge)",
        "فَعَال - often with movement: ذَهَاب، سَفَر"
      ]
    }
  ],
